.SH 13. IMAGES
.TP
cpdf \-list\-images[\-json] [\-inline] in.pdf [<range>]
List the images in a file, together with their object number, page
numbers, image name, width, height, size in bytes, bits per pixel,
colour space, compression method, mask type and mask object number.
Either in plain text (\-list\-images) or JSON (\-list\-images\-json).
.TP
\f[B]\-inline\f[R]
Also list inline images.
.PP
cpdf \-list\-images\-used[\-json] [\-inline] in.pdf [<range>] cpdf
\-image\-resolution[\-json] <n> [\-inline] in.pdf [<range>]
.PP
: The \-list\-images\-used and \-list\-images\-used\-json operations
list the images at point of use, including page number, image name,
width in pixels, height in pixels, x resolution, y resolution and object
number.
Using \-image\-resolution or \-image\-resolution\-json instead reports
only such images as do not reach a minimum resolution.
.TP
\f[B]\-inline\f[R]
Also list inline images.
.PP
cpdf \-extract\-images in.pdf [<range>] [\-im ] [\-p2p ] [\-dedup |
\-dedup\-perpage] [\-raw] [\-inline] [\-merge\-masks] \-o <path>
.PP
