.SH 19. ACCESSIBLE PDFS WITH PDF/UA
.TP
cpdf \-print\-struct\-tree in.pdf
Print a PDF\(cqs structure tree to Standard Output for inspection.
.TP
cpdf \-extract\-struct\-tree in.pdf \-o out.json
Extract the whole structure tree in JSON format.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for details.
.TP
cpdf \-replace\-struct\-tree in.json in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Replace a PDF\(cqs structure tree with one from a JSON file.
.TP
cpdf \-remove\-struct\-tree in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Remove the structure tree from a file.
.TP
cpdf \-mark\-as\-artifact in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Mark all the content of the file as being an artifact.
.TP
cpdf \-verify \(lqPDF/UA\-1(matterhorn)\(rq [\-json] in.pdf
Verify conformance with PDF/UA\-1.
.TP
\f[B]\-json\f[R]
Output conformance failures in JSON rather than plain text format.
.TP
cpdf \-verify \(lqPDF/UA\-1(matterhorn)\(rq \-verify\-single <test> [\-json] in.pdf
Verify conformance with PDF/UA\-1 using just one test.
See cpdfmanual.pdf for list of tests.
.TP
cpdf \-mark\-as [\(lqPDF/UA\-1\(rq | \(lqPDF/UA\-2\(rq] in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Mark a PDF as conforming to PDF/UA\-1 or PDF/UA\-2
.TP
cpdf \-remove\-mark [\(lqPDF/UA\-1\(rq | \(lqPDF/UA\-2\(rq] in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Remove conformance marker from a PDF.
.TP
cpdf \-create\-pdf\-ua\-<1|2> <title> [\-create\-pdf\-pages <n>] [\-create\-pdf\-papersize <paper size>] \-o out.pdf
Create a new, blank, PDF/UA\-1 or PDF/UA\-2 file.
.TP
\f[B]\-create\-pdf\-pages\f[R]
Give the number of pages.
.TP
\f[B]\-create\-pdf\-papersize\f[R]
Give the paper size, e.g \(lqa3landscape\(rq or \(lq200pt 600pt\(rq
.SH 20. MISCELLANEOUS
.TP
cpdf \-draft [\-boxes] [\-draft\-remove\-only <n>] in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Remove bitmapped (photographic) images from a PDF.
.TP
\f[B]\-boxes\f[R]
Replace each image with a crossed box to show where it was.
.TP
\f[B]\-draft\-remove\-only\f[R]
Remove only one image, with the given name.
The name can be obtained from, for example, \-list\-images\-used.
.TP
cpdf \-remove\-all\-text in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Remove all text from a PDF.
.TP
cpdf \-blacktext in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Make all text black.
.TP
cpdf \-blacklines in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Make all lines black.
.TP
cpdf \-blackfills in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Make all fills black.
.TP
cpdf \-thinlines <min thickness> in.pdf [<range>] \-o out.pdf
Make each line a minimum thickness.
A negative value will instead thin lines to the absolute of the value
given.
By processing twice, with a positive then negative figure, it is
therefore possible to clamp thicknesses to a range or single value.
.TP
cpdf \-clean in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Deprecated.
This work is now done by default upon writing any file.
.TP
cpdf \-set\-version <version number> in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Set the version of a PDF.
E.g for version 1.4, use \-set\-version 4.
For PDF versions starting with 2, add ten to the number.
E.g for PDF 2.0, use \-set\-version 10.
.TP
cpdf \-copy\-id\-from source.pdf in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Copy the ID from one PDF to another.
.TP
cpdf \-remove\-id in.pdf \-o out.pdf
Remove the ID from a PDF.
.TP
cpdf \-list\-spot\-colors in.pdf
List the names of any separation colour spaces in a PDF.
